The paper focuses on distributed algorithms in the CONGEST model, which is a well-studied model in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with fundamental problems such as leader election, broadcast, spanning tree, minimum spanning tree, and minimum cut, which are classic problems in computer science and fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). The paper also presents a uniform approach based on constructing a sparsified spanning subgraph, which involves graph theory and falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper presents randomized algorithms, which involve probability theory and fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
